President Biden and Vice President Harris spoke with President Zelenskyy of Ukraine to emphasize that the United States will never recognize Russia's annexation of Ukrainian territory. President Biden promised to continue supporting Ukraine in its defense against Russian aggression, including providing a new $625 million security assistance package that includes weapons and equipment. He also affirmed the United States' readiness to impose severe costs on anyone supporting Russia's annexation. President Biden welcomed the successful agreement allowing the safe export of Ukrainian grain and emphasized the need to maintain this. He also mentioned ongoing efforts to rally the world in support of Ukraine's freedom and democracy.